Work.description:
An abstract creative work (= [LRM Work](http://iflastandards.info/ns/lrm/lrmer/E2)) that has been published in one or
more [publications](/schemas/Publication).

## About work titles

Each work has a preferred title in the `nameParts` property.

For translated works the preferred title will typically be the title
of the work in its *original language, transcribed in Latin script*.
Our data model does not currently include preferred titles for different languages.
If you know the preferred language(s) of the user, it is often a good idea to present a title in one of those languages instead.
To do that, you currently have to loop through the `publications` list and select a title yourself.
Here is a code example in JavaScript:

```javascript
// List of user's languages ordered by preference
const userLanguages = ["nob", "nno", "eng"];

// Function that returns a publication that best matches the list of preferred languages
function findRepresentativePublication(publications) {
  for (const language of userLanguages) {
    for (const publication of publications) {
      if (publication.language == language) {
        return publication;
      }
    }
  }
  // No publication in any of the preferred languages was found, just return the first one.
  if (publications.length) {
    return publications[0];
  }
}
const works = (await fetch('https://bibliografisk.bs.no/works/v0/?query=bovary').then(data => data.json())).results;
for (const work of works) {
  const representativePublication = findRepresentativePublication(work.publications);
  console.log('Representative title: ' + representativePublication?.name);
}
```
